> This delicious Parmigiano and Parma Ham Filled Pasta has been expertly designed by our chefs as a lighter option to help with a balanced lifestyle.

== Mushrooms ==

Boil a full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, heat a generous drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

When hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{120%g} to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{6-8%minutes}.

While the mushrooms are frying, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the mushrooms have browned, add the garlic and fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @vegan 'Nduja{1/2%sachet}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce.

> Use less 'Nduja if you'd prefer things milder.

Simmer the sauce until thickened slightly, ~{3-4%minutes}.

== Pasta ==

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with 1/2 tsp salt and bring back to the boil.

Add the @parma ham & parmigiano reggiano filled pasta{250%g} and cook until tender, ~{3%minutes}.

Once cooked, carefully drain in a #colander{}. Drizzle with oil and gently stir through to stop it sticking together.

== Finishing ==

Once your sauce has thickened, stir the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} through the sauce until melted.

Remove from the heat.

Taste and season with more salt, pepper and sugar to taste.

== To Serve ==

Gently stir your filled pasta through the sauce and share between your #serving bowls{}.

Top with the @wild rocket{20%g} and drizzle some @olive oil{} over the leaves to finish.

Enjoy!